{"default_url":null,"content":{"state":0,"taskInstructions":null,"references":[],"isTaskInstructionsVisible":true,"isCommentMandatory":false,"fields":[],"masterFinding":{"id":690115,"exploitInstructions":"","verificationInstructions":"","remediationInstructions":"Do not store unencrypted social security numbers in any location.  That includes, but is not limited to:\n<ul><li>Binaries</li>\n<li>Configuration files</li>\n<li>Scripts</li>\n<li>Windows registry</li>\n<li>Databases</li>\n</ul>\nUse a strong encryption method to protect social security numbers. Below is a list of potential security controls that can help reduce the risk of sensitive information disclosure.  However, please be aware that each option carries different levels of risk.\n<ul><li>Encrypt data using database server functionality to protect it during run-time</li>\n<li>Encrypt data using the application to protect it during run-time</li>\n<li>Use file-level encryption to protect database and other sensitive files if the disk becomes physically accessible</li>\n<li>Use full disk encryption to protect the database if the disk becomes physically accessible</li>\n<li>Encrypt database and server backups</li>\n</ul>\n","name":"Unencrypted Storage of Social Security Numbers","sourceId":"M:690115","severity":"Medium","businessImpact":"A threat agent may be able to gain unauthorized access to social security numbers through several vectors including, but not limited to:\n*Direct database access from the database server\n*Database access through the application\n*Physical access to the database server hard drive\n*Logical or physical access to the database and server backup tapes and files\n\n In the event of an incident, revenue could be loss due to brand damage, fines, and penalties.","description":"Unencrypted social security numbers were discovered.\n"}}}